  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> rump steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Heat a pot with a lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat, then once hot, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>roasted garlic paste </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant, once fragrant, add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up until the rice is fully coated</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720168802864-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720168802864-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720168802864-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720168802864-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720168802864-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is fully coated, add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]<strong> </span>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat – this is your <strong>seasoned rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720168806365-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
